headline: Dominion Energy (NYSE:D) Faces 9% Price Dip Over Last Quarter
summary: Dominion Energy (NYSE:D) recently came under activist pressure with a proposal by the National Legal and Policy Center to revise executive pay incentives, which the company opposed. Over the last quarter, its share price declined by 9.05%, correlating with broader market turbulence amid significant tariff announcements by the U.S., which also sent the S&P 500 down 12%. Despite these challenges, Dominion Energy's financial standing remained supported by steady dividends and adjusted earnings...
